Singatalur LIS making steady progress  тАв  Barrage and Left Bank Canal works completed тАв  Irrigation facility provided to 97,572 acres of area during the term of the present government тАв  Beneficiary Districts: Ballari, Koppal and Gadag  The Singatalur Lift Irrigation Scheme, which is being implemented to provide irrigation facility to a total area of 2,65,340 acres (flow irrigation for 48,400 acres and drip irrigation for 2,16,940 acres) in Ballari, Koppal and Gadag districts, is making a steady progress during the term of the present government. While the barrage works and the 40.13 km long Right Bank Canal works have been completed, tendering process related to providing irrigation through drip system to a portion of the command area (24,908 acres) under the Left Bank Canal is underway. As of now, irrigation facility has been provided to an area of 97,572 acres during the term of the present government.   - Dr. M. B. Patil, Water Resources & Vijayapura District In-charge Minister

р▓бр▓╛. р▓Ор▓В. р▓мр▓┐. р▓кр▓╛р▓Яр│Ар▓▓, р▓Ьр▓▓р▓╕р▓Вр▓кр▓ир│р▓ор│Вр▓▓ р▓╣р▓╛р▓Чр│В р▓╡р▓┐р▓Ьр▓пр▓кр│р▓░ р▓Ьр▓┐р▓▓р│р▓▓р▓╛ р▓Йр▓╕р│р▓др│р▓╡р▓╛р▓░р▓┐ р▓╕р▓Ър▓┐р▓╡р▓░р│  Tank filling projects have been a major boon for rain-fed and drought-prone areas. Besides providing drinking water to the people and livestock and improving  groundwater tables in these regions, tanks also attract animals, birds and other fauna. Watching animals and birds drinking water from the once parched lakes of Vijayapura is indeed a beautiful sight.  The tank filling projects are being carried out in Koppal, Bagalkot, Mysuru, Yadgir, Belgaum, Vijayapura, Chikballapura, Mandva, Raichur, Uttara Kannada, Udupi, Mangaluru, Chitradurga and Tumkurur districts among others. While some of the projects have been completed, other projects are in various stages of completion.  - Dr. M. B. Patil, Water Resources & Vijayapura District In-charge Minister
